      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOT ROD HARRY (3) put the writing on the wall when he came from one spot wider than this and finished second last time out, beaten 1.2 metres at this venue. Should have no excuses from this advantageous draw so can go one better. WELEASE WODDEWICK (5) scored last time out by 2.5 metres in a good performance at Redcliffe. That made it two wins from his last three having come from a similar barrier to salute at this circuit and distance earlier in the month. Big chance. FIGHT TO THE END (4) is first up for six months having ended last campaign with back-to-back wins here, the most recent coming in the Sunshine Stars 3CG Classic. Has trialled and could pick up where he left off. SCRUFFY NZ (6) must be respected after winning three of his last four starts here, the latest from this barrier.",
